# Cursor Rules — Portfolio Website Build

You are building a personal portfolio website. Before writing any code, read these files in this
package, in order:

1. `01_DESIGN_BRIEF.md` — the visual direction and, critically, the anti-patterns to avoid. Do not
   skip this. The single biggest risk on this project is defaulting to a generic AI-portfolio
   template — this file exists to prevent that.
2. `02_DESIGN_SYSTEM.md` — exact color tokens, typography, spacing, shape language, and motion
   rules. Use these values exactly; do not invent new colors or fonts outside this system.
3. `03_ARCHITECTURE.md` — tech stack, folder structure, routing, and the JSON-driven content
   contract.
4. `04_SECTIONS.md` — the detailed spec for every section, in order.
5. `/data/*.json` — the actual seed content. Some fields contain `TODO:` placeholder text; keep
   these editable and obvious, don't silently invent final copy to replace them unless asked.

## Hard rules
- **Never hardcode copy, project data, skills, or timeline entries inside a component.** Always
  read from the corresponding `/data/*.json` file via a typed loader in `/lib/types.ts`.
- **Never default to a symmetric, centered, card-grid layout** for a section unless
  `04_SECTIONS.md` explicitly says that section should be calm/symmetric (Contact, and the `/work`
  overflow grid).
- The Projects section's 2-3 featured entries must each have a **visually distinct layout
  variant** — reuse of one symmetric `ProjectCard`-style template for all three is a direct
  violation of the brief.
- Use only the three defined type families (Chakra Petch, Big Shoulders Display, Inter) and only
  in the roles assigned to them in `02_DESIGN_SYSTEM.md`.
- Use only the CSS variable color tokens — no arbitrary hex values in component code.
- Build mobile-first, but do not simply stack every asymmetric layout into a single centered
  column on mobile — preserve some of the offset/overlap character at smaller sizes where
  reasonably possible (e.g. an image can still bleed off one edge on mobile).
- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion`.
- TypeScript strict mode. Type every JSON shape in `/lib/types.ts` before building the components
  that consume it.

## Workflow
1. Scaffold the Next.js App Router project and Tailwind config with the design tokens wired in.
2. Build `/lib/types.ts` matching the seed JSON shapes exactly.
3. Build shared primitives in `/components/ui` (Button, Tag, SectionHeading) using the design
   system tokens.
4. Build sections in the order listed in `04_SECTIONS.md`, starting with Hero + VerticalNavRail.
5. Build the Projects section last among the homepage sections — it's the most involved
   (three distinct custom layouts) and should be done once the design language feels established
   from the earlier, simpler sections.
6. Build the `/work` overflow route and optional `/work/[slug]` template.
7. Pass over the whole page for motion polish (scroll reveals, hover states) once structure and
   content are in place — don't animate before layout is settled.

## When in doubt
If a design decision isn't covered by these files, default to the principles in
`01_DESIGN_BRIEF.md` section "Non-negotiable design principles" — asymmetry, confident color
blocking, purposeful type, restrained motion, JSON-driven content — over convenience or the most
common pattern in your training data.
